Function:
A function is a reusable block of code. It can be called anywhere in the program. Main advantage of functions is reusability which means using existing code without writing it every time we need.
You can use same code with different parameters to get results.

JS: 
Keyword=function
()
Parameters=values(variables)which are declared inside the () while defining the functions. 
Arguments: values which are passed through the parameters 
Anonymous Function:
A function without name, after we create a function without name and we assign it to variable
Example:
Sum = function(n1,n2){
Let r = n1+n2
Return r
}console.log(sum(8,9))

